The global antithyroid agents market is segmented based on drug class, route of administration, and application. In terms of drug class, thioamide holds a significant market share due to its effectiveness in managing hyperthyroidism. Iodine solutions are also widely used for their quick action in reducing thyroid hormone levels. Beta blockers and glucocorticoids are prescribed in certain cases to alleviate symptoms associated with hyperthyroidism.

Considering the route of administration, the oral route dominates the market as it is the most convenient method for patients to self-administer medication. However, in emergency situations such as thyroid storm, intravenous administration is preferred for faster onset of action. The application segment is largely driven by the treatment of hyperthyroidism, which is the primary indication for antithyroid agents. Thyroid storm, although less common, requires immediate medical intervention and contributes to a smaller portion of the market.

